Definition: sudden mass fear and anxiety over anticipated events
Example: panic in the stock market; a war scare; a bomb scare led them to evacuate the building
Synonyms: verb, emotion, scare, adj, all, alarming, scary, anxiety, sudden, mass, fear, and, over, anticipated, events, in, the, stock, market, a, war, bomb, led, them, to, evacuate, building
Category: noun.state
